data.comment: The whistle has gone to start the match.
Suwon Bluewings are whistled for offside.
In the minute 7, Suwon Bluewings move into a 0-1 lead through a Doneil Henry header.
Great play from Kim Min-woo to set up the goal.
Corner awarded to Suwon Bluewings.
In the minute 14, Lee Yeong-jae (Gangwon) has been booked and must now be careful not to get a second yellow card.
Throw-in for Suwon Bluewings in their own half.
Suwon Bluewings to take a throw-in in Gangwon territory.
In the minute 16, Gangwon have a goal kick.
The ref points to the spot, it's a penalty for Suwon Bluewings.
Adam Taggart nets and Suwon Bluewings extend their lead to 0-2. The goal came from the penalty spot.
In the minute 20, Suwon Bluewings awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Kim Min-woo (Suwon Bluewings) gets in a strike but the shot is blocked by a defender.
A throw-in for the away team on the opposite half.
In the minute 21, Ball goes out of play for a Gangwon goal kick.
Gangwon takes a corner from the left.
Lee Yeong-jae of Gangwon gets in a strike, but is off target.
In the minute 25, Gangwon drives forward and Ko Mu-yeol gets in a shot. Without netting, however.
Suwon Bluewings will need to be alert as they defend a dangerous free kick from Gangwon.
Lee Yeong-jae of Gangwon smashes in a shot on target. The keeper saves, though.
In the minute 32, Suwon Bluewings are coming forward and Adam Taggart gets in a strike, it misses the target, however.
It's a goal kick for the home team in Chuncheon.
Free kick in a good position for Gangwon!
In the minute 33, Goal kick for Suwon Bluewings at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
Ball safe as Gangwon is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Throw-in for Gangwon at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
In the minute 36, Suwon Bluewings awarded a free kick in their own half.
Throw-in Suwon Bluewings.
Throw-in for Gangwon at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
In the minute 39, Can Gangwon get the ball into an attacking position from this throw-in in Suwon Bluewings's half?
Free kick for Suwon Bluewings in their own half.
Throw-in for Gangwon in their own half.
In the minute 40, Corner awarded to Gangwon.
Free kick for Suwon Bluewings in the half of Gangwon.
Gangwon pushes forward through Kim Kyung-jung, whose finish on goal is saved.
In the minute 45, Throw-in high up the field for Gangwon in Chuncheon.
1 minutes of injury time will be added to the 1st half.
The ref's whistle signals the end of the first-half.
In the minute 46, The second-half is now underway.
Gangwon have a dangerous throw-in.
It's getting dangerous! Free kick for Gangwon close to the penalty box.
In the minute 47, Gangwon are pushing forward but Lee Yeong-jae's finish is wide of the goal.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Chuncheon.
Suwon Bluewings needs to be cautious. Gangwon have an attacking throw-in.
In the minute 49, Throw-in Suwon Bluewings.
Ball safe as Suwon Bluewings is awarded a throw-in in their half.
Gangwon awarded a free kick in their own half.
In the minute 52, Ball goes out of play for a Suwon Bluewings goal kick.
Free kick for Gangwon in their own half.
The away team replace Terry Antonis with Ko Seung-beom.
In the minute 54, Ko Mu-yeol keeps the home team in the match by reducing the deficit to 1-2.
Kim Seung-dae instrumental with a fine assist.
Jang Ho-Ik is booked for the away team.
In the minute 57, Suwon Bluewings awarded a free kick in their own half.
Gangwon takes a corner from the right.
Throw-in for Gangwon in the half of Suwon Bluewings.
In the minute 61, Free kick Gangwon.
In Chuncheon a free kick has been awarded the away team.
In Chuncheon a free kick has been awarded the home team.
In the minute 64, Han Seok-jong (Suwon Bluewings) gets a yellow card.
Gangwon's Lee Yeong-jae is on target but unsuccessful.
Corner awarded to Gangwon.
In the minute 66, Gangwon drive upfield and Lee Yeong-jae gets in a shot. The strike is blocked by a Suwon Bluewings defender.
Free kick for Suwon Bluewings in their own half.
Lee Jae-kwon (Gangwon) has received a first yellow card.
In the minute 67, Kim Gun-hee is writhing in pain and play has been suspended for a few moments.
Free kick Suwon Bluewings.
Kim Gun-hee is back on his feet again.
In the minute 69, Suwon Bluewings are pushing forward but Ko Seung-beom's finish is wide of the goal.
Gangwon have a goal kick.
Suwon Bluewings's Ko Seung-beom misses with an attempt on goal.
In the minute 70, Goal kick for Gangwon at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
Ko Mu-yeol (Gangwon) goes for goal but the shot is blocked by an alert defence.
Gangwon takes a corner from the left.
In the minute 73, Kim Yeong-bin of Gangwon gets in a strike, but is off target.
Ball goes out of play for a Suwon Bluewings goal kick.
Lee Yeong-jae (Gangwon) is given an opening but the shot is blocked by a defender.
In the minute 75, Gangwon takes a corner from the left.
Can Gangwon capitalize from this throw-in deep inside Suwon Bluewings's half?
Gangwon are coming forward and Lee Yeong-jae gets in a strike, it misses the target, however.
In the minute 77, Suwon Bluewings have a goal kick.
Im Sang-hyeob is replacing Adam Taggart for the away team.
Gangwon are in shooting range from this free kick.
In the minute 81, Gangwon make their first substitution with Kim Ji-hyeon replacing Kim Seung-dae.
Jeong Ji-yong is on a sub for Kim Kyung-jung for Gangwon.
Gangwon are pushing forward but Ko Mu-yeol's finish is wide of the goal.
In the minute 83, Kim Tae-hwan is booked for the away team.
It's a goal kick for the away team in Chuncheon.
Throw-in for Suwon Bluewings close to the penalty box.

Throw-in high up the field for Gangwon in Chuncheon.

In the minute 89, Suwon Bluewings awarded a throw-in in their own half.
Throw-in for Gangwon in the half of Suwon Bluewings.
Suwon Bluewings's Jang Ho-Ik misses with an attempt on goal.
In the minute 89, Goal kick for Gangwon at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
Throw-in for Suwon Bluewings at Chuncheon Songam Sports Town.
The fourth official's board shows 4 minutes, which will be added to the 2nd half.

Suwon Bluewings awarded a free kick in their own half.
Corner awarded to Gangwon.
Throw-in for Gangwon in their own half.
The match is over. Final score 1-2.
Kim Joon-hyung is replacing Kim Min-woo for the away team.
